  "local_port": 51352,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why does a window on my iPad keep popping up saying: \"No SIM card installed\u201d?",
  "response": "The \"No SIM card installed\" message on your iPad typically appears when the device is unable to detect a SIM card in its SIM tray. Here are some possible reasons why this might be happening, along with solutions:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **SIM Card Not Inserted**\n   - If your iPad is a cellular model but doesn\u2019t have a SIM card installed, the message will appear. \n   - **Solution**: Insert a compatible SIM card into the SIM tray.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **SIM Card Not Properly Seated**\n   - The SIM card might not be inserted correctly or could be loose.\n   - **Solution**: Turn off your iPad, eject the SIM tray, and reinsert the SIM card carefully. Ensure it\u2019s properly seated.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Damaged or Faulty SIM Card**\n   - The SIM card could be damaged, scratched, or faulty.\n   - **Solution**: Try using the SIM card in another device to confirm if it\u2019s working. If it\u2019s damaged, contact your carrier for a replacement.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **iPad SIM Tray or Reader Issue**\n   - The SIM tray or the SIM card reader on your iPad might be damaged or malfunctioning.\n   - **Solution**: Inspect the SIM tray for damage. If the issue persists, contact Apple Support or visit an Apple Store for repair.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Software Glitch**\n   - A temporary software issue could cause the iPad to incorrectly detect the SIM card.\n   - **Solution**: Restart your iPad. If that doesn\u2019t work, update to the latest version of iPadOS.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Non-Cellular iPad Model**\n   - If your iPad model does not support cellular connectivity, it will show this message when trying to access cellular settings.\n   - **Solution**: Check your iPad\u2019s model to confirm if it supports cellular. If not, the message is irrelevant and can be ignored.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Carrier Settings Issue**\n   - There might be an issue with the carrier settings or the SIM card is not activated/configured properly.\n   - **Solution**: Contact your carrier to ensure the SIM card is activated and compatible with your iPad.\n\n---\n\nIf you\u2019ve tried these steps and the issue persists, it\u2019s best to contact Apple Support or your carrier for further assistance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
